g.text: Normalized BDS-compatible data: Chains, Blocks, Transactions, Events, ...
How consumers express filters for data they care about.
How relationships are requested and exposed (e.g. events of a transaction)
Technology to deliver the data to consumer. (e.g REST, gRPC binary, Apache Arrow)
Libraries for common transport solutions (e.g .proto files, Arrow definitions, etc)
Index and process raw normalized BDS-compatible data to generated business-specific models.
Subgraph and Ponder are at this level focused on end-user products.
